import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('date')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['date'], data_grouped['rate'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2010 = data[data['year'] == 2010]
    industry_rate = data_2010.groupby('series')['rate'].mean()
    industry_rate.sort_values(ascending=False, inplace=True)
    
    ax = industry_rate.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_xlabel('Industry')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?', wrap=True)
    
    max_rate = industry_rate.max()
    ax.axhline(max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Rate: {max_rate:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2005 = data[data['year'] == 2005]
    grouped_data = data_2005.groupby('series')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    max_unemployment = grouped_data['count'].max()
    
    ax = grouped_data.plot.bar(x='series', y='count', legend=False)
    ax.axhline(max_unemployment, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_unemployment:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("Which industry had the highest number of unemployed individuals in 2005?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.boxplot(data['rate'])
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks([1], ['All Industries'])
    avg_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate across all industries?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
